ce:section.ce:para:
The protein immobilization of the as-prepared CCF, A-MFNPs-3, B-MFNPs-3 and B-MFNPs-5 using BSA as the model protein were investigated. The effect of contact time on the immobilization of template protein by MFNPs is shown in Fig. 6
                        a. As seen, the immobilization was fast initially, and slowed down thereafter, and reached equilibrium finally. In the case of B-MFNPs-5, the maximum immobilization of BSA is attained at 80 min. Compared with the previous researches (Table 1
                        ), we found a higher adsorption capacity of 59.12 mg g−1 for B-MFNPs-5 samples. The relative fast adsorption rate can be potentially owing to the nanosized thickness of the biomass layer assembled on the NPs. Thus, the contact time of 150 min is enough to reach equilibrium for MFNPs in the BSA immobilization, which was chosen in the further experiments.
